author: GameSpot
description:
The fun in Black Ops 7 is fueled by well-designed maps and futuristic themes.

Call of Duty fatigue has been building up for some time. We've reached over two decades of yearly CoD releases, and this year delivers a second consecutive year of Black Ops. Going back-to-back with Black Ops 7 feels risky, but Treyarch clearly listened to community feedback and delivered several changes to prevent this year from an overly familiar feel. Treyarch brings a futuristic era, improved omnimovement, and strong map design with Black Ops 7, which greatly enhances the experience from last year. Black Ops 7 multiplayer is still adrenaline-fueled fun, but this year gives you new tech to play with and more room to breathe.

Credits: S.E. Doster, Ben Janca, Erick Tay

#cod #blops7 #callofduty #blackops
title: Call of Duty: Black Ops 7 Multiplayer Review - Strong Map Design Makes Multiplayer A Blast

description:
The Xbox Partner Preview is coming November 20th, 2025 to showcase upcoming games from Xbox's talented third-party partners. Tune in for news, announcements, trailers and more from partners including IO Interactive, Tencent and THQ Nordic, plus some brand-new reveals and Game Pass announcements.

Additionally, Jennifer English, who portrays Tides of Annihilation protagonist Gwendolyn, will be the voiceover artist for the show.
